The paper deals with algorithms for computing short paths on polytopes, which is a topic related to computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of matrices and determinants suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The mention of a parameter that measures the flatness of the vertices of the polytope suggests that numerical analysis (cs.NA) may also be relevant. Finally, the paper discusses the running time of the algorithm, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
